nd services based on their actual consumption. By doing so, ABC helps in more accurately tracing costs to products and services. The method allocates overheads to products based on activities that drive costs, such as machine setups, machine running, procurement, and delivery.\",9\n1574,\"\"\"EVALUATING THE IMPACT OF ACTIVITY-BASED COSTING ON PRICING STRATEGIES AT BBB\"\"\",\"\"\"Brick By Brick (BBB) provides a range of building services, including garage conversions (GC) and extensions to properties (EX). BBB has a policy to price all jobs at budgeted total cost plus 50%. Overheads are currently absorbed on a labour hour basis. However, BBB has found that it has fewer GC contracts than expected, and it believes that this is because the current overhead absorption method apportions an excessive amount of overheads to GC, leading to a price that is uncompetitive. The company is now considering moving to an activity-based cost approach.\"\"\",6\n1576,\"\"\"CURRENT METHOD OF ABSORBING OVERHEADS\"\"\",\"\"\"The current method of absorbing overheads at BBB is based on labour hours.\"\"\",2\n1577,\"\"\"SALES PRICE FOR A TYPICAL GC USING CURRENT METHOD\"\"\",\"\"\"Price per unit using absorption cost plus 50%: Materials: $3,500, Labour (300 * 15): $4,500, Overheads (300 * ($400,000/40,000)): $3,000, Total cost: $11,000, Plus mark-up (50%): $5,500, Current price: $16,500.\"\"\",2\n1578,\"\"\"COST OF A GC USING ACTIVITY-BASED COSTING\"\"\",\"\"\"Cost per unit using activity-based costing: Materials: $3,500, Labour (300 * 15): $4,500, Overheads: Supervisors (1 * 180): $180, Planners (1 * 280): $280, Property related (300 * 6): $1,800, Total cost: $10,260.\"\"\",2\n1579,\"\"\"COST PER UNIT OF A TYPICAL EX USING ACTIVITY-BASED COSTING\"\"\",\"\"\"Cost per unit of a typical EX using activity-based costing: Materials: $8,000, Labour (500 * 15): $7,500, Overheads: Supervisors (6 * 180): $1,080, Planners (5 * 280): $1,400, Property related (500 * 6): $3,000, Total cost: $20,980, Th